#! /bin/bash

set -eux

echo "### INSTALL PACKAGES ------------------->>>>"
apt-get update -y
apt-get install python-minimal python-pip -y
chronyc tracking
chronyc sources

# apt-get install ntpstat -y
# apt-get install ntp -y
# ntpq -pcrv


echo "### SETUP DATA MOUNT ------------------->>>>"

function prep_disk {

local product=$1
local disk_role=$2
local device=$3

cat <<EOF > /etc/systemd/system/opt-${product}-${disk_role}.automount
[Unit]
Description=Automount opt/${product}/${disk_role}

[Automount]
Where=/opt/${product}/${disk_role}

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
EOF

cat <<EOF > /etc/systemd/system/opt-${product}-${disk_role}.mount
[Unit]
Description=Mount opt/${product}/${disk_role}

[Mount]
What=/dev/${device}
Where=/opt/${product}/${disk_role}
Type=xfs
Options=defaults,nofail
EOF


cat <<EOF > /etc/systemd/system/initialize-opt-${product}-${disk_role}-mount.service 
[Unit]
Description=Formats and preps the DATA dir
Before=opt-${product}-${disk_role}.mount
Before=opt-${product}-${disk_role}.automount
Wants=opt-${product}-${disk_role}.automount 

[Service]
Type=oneshot
RemainAfterExit=yes

Environment='DIR_OWNER=root' 'DIR_PATH=/opt/${product}/${disk_role}'

# Backup existing directory
ExecStartPre=/bin/mkdir -p \${DIR_PATH}

# Formats the disk if it is brand new
ExecStart=/bin/bash -c \
  "(blkid -t TYPE=xfs | grep /dev/${device}) \
  || (wipefs -fa /dev/${device} && mkfs.xfs /dev/${device})"

# Sets the appropriate permission
ExecStartPost=/bin/bash -c \
  "(ls -ld \${DIR_PATH} | grep -P \s\${DIR_OWNER}\s) \
  || (id -u \${DIR_OWNER} && chown \${DIR_OWNER}:\${DIR_OWNER} \${DIR_PATH})"

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
EOF


systemctl enable initialize-opt-${product}-${disk_role}-mount.service opt-${product}-${disk_role}.automount 
systemctl start initialize-opt-${product}-${disk_role}-mount.service 


}

prep_disk dse data nvme0n1
prep_disk dse backup xvdb
